---
import ArticleLayout from '../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbLd } from '../lib/jsonld';
const path = '/terms/';
const crumbs = [{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'terms', path }];
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="Terms of Use | PrivacyKit"
  description="The terms for using PrivacyKit's free browser tools: provided as-is with no warranty, not professional advice, acceptable use, liability and Australian law."
  path={path}
  h1="terms"
  crumbs={crumbs}
  jsonLd={[breadcrumbLd(crumbs)]}
>
  <p><em>Last updated: 3 July 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    These terms govern your use of PrivacyKit (the "site") and the tools it
    provides. By using the site you agree to them. If you do not agree, please
    do not use the site. The tools are free, and these terms are the trade-off
    for that: they set out what you can expect and what you cannot.
  </p>

  <h2>The tools are provided as-is</h2>
  <p>
    Everything on PrivacyKit is offered without warranty of any kind, express or
    implied, to the fullest extent the law allows. That includes no guarantee
    that a tool is free of bugs, that it will produce a correct or complete
    result, that it will be available at any given time, or that it is fit for a
    particular purpose. The tools are built carefully and their methods are
    documented, but you use them at your own risk and should verify any result
    that matters.
  </p>

  <h2>Not professional advice</h2>
  <p>
    PrivacyKit's tools and guides are informational. They are not legal,
    security, financial, or other professional advice, and using them does not
    create any professional relationship. A password-strength estimate, a breach
    check, an EXIF report, or a generated privacy policy is a starting point, not
    a substitute for advice from a qualified professional about your specific
    situation. Decisions with real consequences — legal, security, or
    otherwise — should be checked with someone qualified.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You may use the tools for any lawful purpose. You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>use the site to break the law or to infringe anyone's rights;</li>
    <li>
      attempt to disrupt, overload, or interfere with the site or the services
      it depends on, including automated scraping that degrades it for others;
    </li>
    <li>
      use the tools to attack, gain unauthorised access to, or test systems you
      do not own or have permission to test — for example, running a domain or a
      password through a tool as part of an attack on someone else; or
    </li>
    <li>
      misrepresent the site's output as your own professional certification.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The tools run on your device, so how you use them is your responsibility.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, PrivacyKit and its operator are not
    liable for any loss or damage — direct, indirect, incidental, consequential,
    or otherwise — arising from your use of, or inability to use, the site or its
    tools. This includes any loss of data, loss of profits, or harm resulting
    from reliance on a tool's output. Where liability cannot be excluded under
    the Australian Consumer Law, it is limited to the maximum extent that law
    allows.
  </p>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>
    The site links to third-party websites, including affiliate links and the
    external services that a few tools rely on. Those sites are outside
    PrivacyKit's control. Their content, products, and privacy practices are
    their own, and a link is not an endorsement of everything on the
    destination. Once you follow a link, that site's terms and policies apply,
    not these.
  </p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The site's own content and code are the property of its operator, except
    where third-party open-source components are used under their own licences —
    those are credited on the <a href="/licenses/">licenses page</a>. You may
    freely use the tools and their output; you may not republish the site's
    written content wholesale as your own.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    PrivacyKit is operated from Australia, and these terms are governed by the
    laws of Australia. Any dispute relating to the site or these terms is subject
    to the jurisdiction of the Australian courts, and nothing in these terms
    limits any rights you have under the Australian Consumer Law that cannot be
    excluded.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    These terms may be updated from time to time. When they change, the date at
    the top of this page will be revised, and continuing to use the site after
    that means you accept the revised terms. For questions about anything here,
    see the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
